Class DataObjectPackage

  • Object
    • DataObjectPackage

  • public class DataObjectPackage
extends Object
    The Class DataObjectPackage

    Abstract super class for SEDA messages containing a ArchiveTransfer.

    • Method Detail

      • addArchiveUnit

        public void addArchiveUnit(ArchiveUnit au)
                    throws SEDALibException
        Adds an ArchiveUnit as an DataObjectPackage element, defining a uniqID if not already defined (null).

        This is only useful when you create an ArchiveUnit without giving an outer DataObjectPackage in constructor, for example during json deserialization.

        Parameters:
        au - the ArchiveUnit
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - when the ArchiveUnit has a defined UniqId which is already in the DataObjectPackage

      • addDataObjectGroup

        Parameters:

        Throws:

      • addTouchedInDataObjectPackageId

        public void addTouchedInDataObjectPackageId(String inDataObjectPackageId)
        Adds the ArchiveUnit or DataObject inDataPackageObjectId in the touched map, with a count value set to 1.

        This is used when going through all the ArchiveUnits of the graph so has to be sure to treat them only one time, for example when exporting to XML or when searching for the list of roots after an import from xml

        Parameters:
        inDataObjectPackageId - the id in DataObjectPackage

        Parameters:
        inDataObjectPackageId - the id in DataObjectPackage

      • getNextInDataObjectPackageID

        public String getNextInDataObjectPackageID()
        Gets the next ID to use in DataObjectPackage.

        It uses the idCounter to generate an ID in the "IDxxx" form. It tests if this ID is already used, and if so increment idCounter till the ID is uniq.

        Returns:
        the next ID in DataObjectPackage

      • getNextRefID

        public String getNextRefID()
        Gets the next RefID to use in ArchiveTransfer.

        It uses the refIdCounter to generate an ID in the "RefIDxxx" form.

        Returns:
        the next RefID in ArchiveTransfer

      • resetRefIdCounter

        public void resetRefIdCounter()
        Reset refID counter to value 1.

        This counter is used to generate the RefIDs in the manifest during export

      • resetIdCounter

        public void resetIdCounter()
        Reset ID counter to value 10.

        This counter is used to generate the IDs in the manifest during import. It begins at 10 to prevent an id collision with those used in headers of SEDA messages

      • getDescription

        public String getDescription()
        Gets the summary description of DataObjectPackage.

        It list the number of ArchiveUnits, DataObjectGroup, BinaryDataObject (with size in bytes) and PhysicalDatObject

        Returns:
        the description String

                   throws SEDALibException

        Throws:

      • verifyDogUnicityCapacity

        public void verifyDogUnicityCapacity()
                              throws SEDALibException
        Verify if all DataObject lists in ArchiveUnit can be reduced to one DataObjectGroup.
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - if one not reducible DataObject list is detected or a DataObjectGroup has a LogBook wrong format

      • normalizeUniqDataObjectGroup

        public void normalizeUniqDataObjectGroup()
                                  throws SEDALibException
        Normalize each ArchiveUnit to set a uniq DataObjectGroup with all the DataObjects inside.
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - if one not reducible DataObject list is detected or one DataObjectGroup can't be merge due to LogBook wrong format. Important: nothing has been modified in the DataObjectPackage.

      • regenerateContinuousIds

        public void regenerateContinuousIds()
        Regenerate all IDs of ArchiveUnits, DataObjectGroup, BinaryDataObject and PhysicalDataObject in incremented IDxxx form.

      • vitamNormalize

        public void vitamNormalize()
                    throws SEDALibException
        Normalize the structure in Vitam standard form:
        • verify that there's no cycle in the ArchiveUnit graph
        • verify that it's possible to get only one DataObjectGroup by ArchiveUnit
        • for each ArchiveUnit set a uniq DataObjectGroup with all the DataObjects inside
        and set the vitamNormalizationStatus value.
        Throws:
        SEDALibException - if one verification fail. Important: nothing has been modified in the DataObjectPackage.
